This paper deals with video processing and motion magnification using deep neural networks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper specifically focuses on physiological visualization, which falls under the category of multimedia (cs.MM). The use of deep neural networks for video processing also falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper discusses the potential applications of their method in healthcare, which falls under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
